              I worry about the wording of the bill being so video distribution focused; the points and provisions made are sensible, but tailoring the bill to video traffic specifically simply opens the door for the same kind of behaviour on a different kind of traffic down the road (audio, streamed web applications, etc...) - why not just make the bill target generic content?

              

              
              
            </div>
