              Argh, more dancing around the issue.   Hey, let's pass a zillion bills that enact net-neutrality piece-by-piece, with lots of omissions and loopholes, creating a complex tapestry of regulation, instead of... just freaking passing a net-neutrality bill.  <br /><br />Better than nothing, but I'd rather have a comprehensive law that mandates that ISPs be dumb pipes, rather than a regulatory nightmare that requires an ever-larger population of lawyers to understand.<br /><br />edited: typos

              

              
              
